summary: lord brandon “petty three eyed eaven” stark of winterfell is my favorite character and the only queen i want on that iron...
body:
lord brandon “petty three eyed eaven” stark of winterfell is my favorite character and the only queen i want on that iron throne.

•sis always gets the tea still piping hot.

•waits for the most inconvenient and inappropriate moment to spill said tea.

•watches the drama unfold in real time (and can rewind that shit with just a roll of his eyes).

•keeps information to himself. (its not his business nor fault that rhaegal is gonna swim with the fishes. it’s not his dragon lol.)

•checks out whenever a conversation doesn’t involve gossip, then clocks back in time to make a situation awkward/tense.

•can you say U N B O T H E R E D?;

-“you wanna go south and fight for dany knowing how terribly it’s gone for stark men down there since our grandfather and uncle? do you, cuz. i’m not the one fucking my aunt.”

-“you wanna leave home (and your siblings) and go murder cersei? alright baby girl. safe travels.”

-“you wanna snitch twenty minutes after promising to keep it a secret then play these motherfuckers in a game of political chess they don’t even know they’re in? if it is what you desire, go off sister, i’m only here to watch.”

•sis is gonna outlive E V E R Y O N E


wow. i stan one (1) petty queen

summary: hello Sayruq! do you have leaks/info about Sansa and Bran in ep4? all the leaks i've read don't mention them :(
question: hello Sayruq! do you have leaks/info about Sansa and Bran in ep4? all the leaks i've read don't mention them :(
answer:
Sorry I didn’t answer this on time. My head was hurting badly and I was looking for the episode on Freefolk. Honestly Sansa and Bran never get mentioned in leaks which freaks people out about whether or not they’ll appear in the ep and then they do. So far the ep 5 & 6 leaks that we have say that Sansa and Bran will be in KL and they will become crowned. Bran (named after Brandon the Rebuilder) will apparently become king of Westeros while Sansa is named Queen in the North.

In the books Bran is the first Starkling to become lord and he was doing the work that comes with it despite being 9. Just because he left to go save the world doesn’t mean he’d irrelevant in a post Other world. Sansa has so much queen imagery and foreshadowing in her arc and she’s acting lady of Eyrie. Jon was lord commander of the Night’s Watch until he got stabbed to death. I assumed he’d become king but it’s likely the Night’s Watch will be restarted.

summary: I feel like Bran is seeming more and more "human" each episode. Especially this episode. Telling Tyrion he shouldn't envy him,...
question: I feel like Bran is seeming more and more "human" each episode. Especially this episode. Telling Tyrion he shouldn't envy him, and he mostly lives in the past. Also, that look he gave before there was a cut scene. I also like how Tyrion is taking interest in Bran, most of the time the show doesn't bother showing people talking to him personally, I like it. I really hope they are heading with Bran regaining more of his humanity by the end of this series. I think it'd be so sad if he doesn't.
answer: When Isaac said we will see a more human Bran, I was disappointment when the show continued sidelining him and treating him like a plot device so I was pleasantly surprised by his scene with Tyrion. I really hope as time goes on we get more of the Bran we’ve always had, the brave, selfless boy who expressed his emotions and did the best that he could
